51.4	Scotch_bonnet_(pepper)	Scotch bonnet (pepper)	Scotch Bonnet, also known as Boabs Bonnet, Scotty Bons, Bonney peppers, or Caribbean red peppers is a variety of chili pepper. Found mainly in the Caribbean islands, it is also in Guyana, the Maldives Islands and west Africa, it is named for its resemblance to a Tam o'shanter hat. Most Scotch Bonnets have a heat rating of 100,000–350,000 Scoville Units. For comparison, most jalapeño peppers have a heat rating of 2,500 to 8,000 on the Scoville scale.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Scotch-bonnet.jpg/220px-Scotch-bonnet.jpg
